-- Evraz Siberian Units Halt Operations on Quake, RIA Novosti Says
-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2011-12-28T09:06:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/evraz-siberian-units-halt-operations-on-quake-ria-novosti-says.html
Evraz Plc’s mining units in Siberia
suspended operations after an earthquake in the Tuva region,  RIA
Novosti  reported, citing a company official it didn’t identify.  Evraz has evacuated workers from mines, the news service
said, adding that the company’s steel mill is operating as
normal. The magnitude 6.7 earthquake struck Tuva late yesterday,
according to the government.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow at 
